  "description": "This\u00a0first-year Glaucous-winged Gull\u00a0was resting on the ice among other gulls the entire time I saw it. \u00a0It was as large as the largest Herring Gulls present. \u00a0The bird was a pale grayish brown. \u00a0Color did not vary noticeably from the mantle to the tertials to the folded primaries. \u00a0Whitish edges were seen on the tips of the primaries. \u00a0Some dusky shading was seen around the eye. \u00a0The bill was long, very thick, and entirely black.",
